'Seychelles' ( ; French: ), officially the 'Republic of Seychelles' (; Creole:
Repiblik Sesel), is a 115-island country spanning an archipelago in the Indian
Ocean, some east of mainland Africa, northeast of the island of Madagascar.

Other nearby island countries and territories include Zanzibar to the west,
Mauritius, Rodrigues, AgalÃ©ga and RÃ©union to the south, and Comoros and Mayotte
to the southwest. Seychelles, with an estimated population of 86,525, has the
smallest population of any African state. It has the highest Human
Development Index in Africa and the highest income inequality in the world, as
measured by the Gini index. Seychelles is a member of the African Union.
